ce:section.ce:para:
Thermal properties of the starch-based samples were measured by a Perkin-Elmer DSC Diamond-8000 with a refrigerated cooling system and nitrogen purge gas was used. Sample powder (5 mg on a dry basis) was weighed into a high-pressure stainless-steel pan (PE No. B0182901) followed by an addition of ∼10 μL of deionized water. Then they were sealed and kept for 24 h at room temperature before measurements. The sample was heated from 30 to 100 °C at a rate of 10 °C/min. An empty pan was served as a reference. The peak (T

                              P
                           ) temperatures and the gelatinization enthalpy (△H) were recorded based on triplicate measurements.
